Diplomatic Ties at Ambassadorial Level Established between DPRK and United Arab Emirates 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- A joint communique on the establishment of diplomatic ties between the governments of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and the United Arab Emirates was made public in New York on September 17. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to it, the governments of the two countries decided to establish diplomatic ties at ambassadorial level effective from the date of signing the joint communique, out of their desire to promote the mutual interests of their peoples and strengthen friendship and cooperation, on the basis of the principles and purpose of the United Nations Charter, especially the international law and treaties on the promotion of international peace and security, equality among nations, national sovereignty, independence, territorial integrity and noninterference in the internal affairs of other countries and in conformity with the provisions of the Vienna Convention on diplomatic relations dated April 18, 1961. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint communique was signed by Pak Kil Yon, DPRK permanent representative and ambassador e. p. to the United Nations, on behalf of the DPRK government and Ahmed Al-Jarman, permanent representative of the United Arab Emirates and its ambassador e. p. to the United Nations, on behalf of its government.

Visits 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- A DPRK delegation led by Choe Su Hon, vice-foreign minister, left here today to participate in the 62nd session of the UN General Assembly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saaeed Eleia Dawood, director of the Organizational Department of the Syria's Baath Arab Socialist Party, and his party arrived here on the same day.

Congratulations to Russian PM 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Il, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, sent a congratulatory message to Viktor Alekseyevich Zubkov upon his appointment as Prime Minister of the government of the Russian Federation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message wished him success in his performance of the responsible job for the prosperity of the country and the well-being of the people.

Greetings to PM of Belize  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Il, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, sent a message of greetings to Said Musa, Prime Minister of Belize, on the occasion of the 26th anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message wished the Belizean prime minister greater success in his responsible work for the progress and prosperity of the country and expressed the belief that the bilateral ties of friendship and cooperation would continue to develop on good terms in the future, too.

FM of DPRK Meets New Cuban Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- Pak Ui Chun, foreign minister of the DPRK, met and had a talk with new Cuban Ambassador to the DPRK Jose Manuel Galego Montano who paid a courtesy call on him today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were officials concerned and a staff member of the Cuban embassy here.

35th Plenary Meeting of Youth League Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hamhung, September 20 (KCNA) -- The 35th plenary meeting of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League was held in Hamhung on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting discussed the issue of arousing the organizations of the youth league to thoroughly implement the tasks proposed in Kim Jong Il's work "Let Young People Highly Exalt the Honor of Being Young Vanguard in the Era of Songun by Carrying Forward the Tradition of the Juche-Oriented Youth Movement" and matters related to frustrating the imperialists' ideological and cultural poisoning. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reporter and speakers at the meeting said that the work published on the occasion of the 80th anniversary of the Young Communist League of Korea serves as a powerful ideological and theoretical weapon for glorifying the idea of the Workers' Party of Korea and the leader, which calls for giving importance to young people, and their leadership exploits and strengthening and developing the youth league into the young vanguard true to the cause of the Party in name and reality and a banner of struggle and advance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting proposed tasks facing the organizations of the youth league to prepare the young people as vanguard fighters of Songun who take the lead in upholding the idea and leadership of Kim Jong Il and ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the harmful and serious impact the imperialists' ideological and cultural poisoning has on the young people, the meeting underscored the need for the organizations of the youth league to become first-line standard-bearers in the anti-imperialist class front and foil the despicable moves of enemies with a revolutionary offensive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting called on all organizations of the youth league and young people to creditably discharge the missions and duties they have assumed before the era and the revolution in the general march of Songun revolution, united close around Kim Jong Il, and thus add shine to the glorious history of the Korean youth movement which has always emerged victorious.

Aphorism on Revolutionary Comradeship 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- "Revolutionary comradeship is the acme of the love for the human being." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The aphorism of Kim Jong Il means that there is no love loftier and more beautiful than the revolutionary comradeship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary comradeship is a noble ideological emotion with which comrades love and value each other. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The love among the revolutionary comrades who share weal and woe, overcoming difficulties and ordeals in the revolutionary struggle is deeper and more enthusiastic than the paternal love or amity among friends. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of the Korean revolution struggle is that of revolutionary comradeship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung made a 40 kilometer-long journey for a comrade overnight during the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle and did not hesitate to throw his life before the enemy's gun for the sake of comrades. His fervent comradeship gave origin to the revolutionary comradeship along with the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Charmed by his rare love, the young revolutionaries of the new generation regarded the President as the centre of leadership and unity and remained loyal to him in the noble sense of the revolutionary obligation till the last moments of their lives. They thus made the history of unity and cohesion, the source of the inexhaustible strength of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of the comradeship made in the Korean revolution under the President is creditably carried forward by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Numerous are anecdotes on comradeship created during his long journey for field guidance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He visited Chol Pass, Mt. Osong, Panmunjom and other places where servicepersons live to help them to feel the pride and honor and had photo session with them in trenches. Looking up to him, they evinced their resolution to live and struggle as eternal Songun revolutionary comrades of the tender-hearted Supreme Commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the servicepersons and people successfully concluded the "Arduous March' and forced march and are now making efforts to build a great prosperous and powerful nation. The credit for this goes to him who took care of and trusted them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the high level of revolutionary comradeship seen in the DPRK constitutes the foundation of the ideological cohesion and unity prevailing in the whole society and source of the invincible strength of the revolutionary ranks.

Art Performance Mirrors Workers' Firm Faith and Will
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- The performance of Art circle members of the Hungnam Fertilizer Complex was given before capacity audience at the People's Palace of Culture in Pyongyang, which began on September 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It fully reflected the invariable faith of the Korean working class to thoroughly adhere to the socialist principle, revolutionary principle, in any adversity and their revolutionary optimism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In satiric dialogue "The voice of Hungnam," choral recitation "Let us add luster to the revolutionary heritage of the fatherly leader under the leadership of the great General," wind instrument music and song "May, Month of Victory" and other numbers, the performers gave impressive presentation of the immortal feats the peerlessly great persons performed at the complex. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Drum and song "General on a Galloping White Horse" which involved over 80 people and instrumental music and song "Ballad of Mt. Singo" and other numbers touched the heart strings of the audience for their unique form of works that could be created only in working site seething with worthwhile labor and life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Duet "Following the General" and "We are a worker-couple" sung by a discharged soldier-couple mirrored the faith and will of the workers that they are sure to win when they firmly believe in and follow leader Kim Jong Il in whatever ordeals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vice-minister of Chemical Industry Pak Chol, when interviewed, said that the repertoire is full of the heroic stamina and enthusiasm of the working class and helps feel the worth and pride of labor. I came to more keenly feel again that the true life can be seen among workers and only the art pieces created at working sites can be popular among the people, he added.

Unity Is Decisive Guarantee for Nation's Independent Reunification: Rodong Sinmun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- To realize the unity of the whole nation is a decisive guarantee for achieving independent and peaceful reunification, says Rodong Sinmun in an article Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The author of the article continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korea's reunification is not for eliminating any contradiction or institutional confrontation within the nation, but for rejoining the blood vessel of the nation cut off by outside forces and realizing national harmony. So the unity of the nation is the great premise and main content of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is unbearable national misfortune and tragedy that the Korean nation has been forced to suffer the pain of division for over 60 years, bisected into the north and the south by outside forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main point in reunifying the country is not certain matters of procedure and method but the achievement of the unity of the whole nation. The main point will be resolved in achieving the   reunification of the country, if the north and the south realize harmony and all the fellow countrymen put their minds together and, on this basis, attain great unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Achievement of the unity of the nation is the main propelling force and the decisive factor in reunifying the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reunification of the country can be successfully achieved only when the whole Korean nation strengthens the internal force of reunification in every way, closely united in one as the force responsible for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality in the June 15 era of reunification in which the struggle for national reconciliation and unity is developing to a new higher plane under the banner of "By our nation itself" eloquently proves the might and vitality of great national unity as the propelling force of the cause of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unity of the nation can be successfully realized if it advances in close unity, irrespective of idea and system, in conformity with the idea of "By our nation itself", the banner of the national unity.

Kim Jong Il's Work Off Press in Mexico
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il's famous work "The Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy" was brought out in booklet by the Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism on Sept. 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work published on July 26, Juche 85 (1996) scientifically deals with the limitation of the time the preceding philosophy was enunciated and the originality of the Juche philosophy and clarifies the idea that the Juche philosophy serves as a revolutionary and political philosophy of the Workers' Party of Korea and issues of principle arising in studying, explaining and disseminating the Juche philosophy.

Special Write-ups on DPRK Posted on Internet Homepages in Various Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- Institutions and organizations in Syria, Britain, Peru and the U.S. posted special write-ups on their Internet homepages on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Syrian Arab News Agency (SANA) posted a photo of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il on Mt. Paektu and an article on its Internet homepage on Sept. 5 to mark the day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The British Association for the Study of Songun Policy posted a photo of the President announcing a political platform of the DPRK government at the 1st session of the Supreme People's Assembly and an article on its Internet homepage on Sept. 7. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage in the article introduced the glorious history of 59 years covered by the DPRK and stressed that the President would always live in the hearts of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Peru Group for the Study of Kimilsungism in an article titled "Spirit of Thaechon" posted on its Internet homepage on Sept. 6 noted that the cause of building a great prosperous powerful nation is a sacred cause of implementing the last instructions of the President in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics in an article titled "Songun Korea would shine forever" posted on its Internet homepage fully introduced in detail the immortal exploits the President performed by founding and developing the DPRK. The DPRK is demonstrating its might as a socialist power thanks to the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il, it added.

Functions Held in Mongolia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- Meetings and art performances took place at Kim Il Sung Kindergarten in Ovorhangay Province and Kim Jong Il Kindergarten in Darkhan-Uul Province of Mongolia on September 8 and 11 on the occasion of the 15th anniversary of naming them after the peerlessly great men and the 59th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the functions were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos showing their revolutionary activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The governor of Ovorhangay Province said in his speech at a meeting that it is pride and honor for his province to have the kindergarten bearing the august name of Kim Il Sung, expressing the will to make a positive contribution to the development of the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Directors of Kim Il Sung Kindergarten in Ovorhangay Province and Kim Jong Il Kindergarten in Darkhan-Uul Province said with deep emotion about the loving care and benevolence shown by Kim Jong Il and evinced their resolutions to bring up children into excellent pillars of the country so as to help them make contributions to successfully inheriting and developing the friendly and cooperative relations with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed art performances given by children.

DPRK's Birthday Celebrated in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 20 (KCNA) -- Meetings took place in Democratic Congo and Sweden and a meeting, book and photo exhibition and film show were held in Austria from September 4 to 7 on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the functions were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, photos showing their immortal feats and books and photos introducing the shining course covered by the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Otete Gaston Mboyo, chairman of the National Committee of the Genuine Lumumbist Patriotic Party of Democratic Congo, praised the DPRK for having advanced only along the road of victory under the banner of Songun, adding that the DPRK would always win victory after victory under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Christer Lundgren, chairman of the Sweden-Korea Friendship Association, noted that the achievements made by the DPRK in the international arena in recent days proved that the way of Songun chosen by the Korean people was right.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Erich Zavadil, chairman of the Consultative Committee of the Society for the Promotion of the Relations between Austria and DPRK, expressed hope that the Korean people would achieve greater success in their struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation and accelerate the reunification of the country under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film show watched Korean film "The country taking on more beautiful looks under the leadership of the great general." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings held in Sweden and Austria.

RPDC y Emiratos Arabes Unidos establecen relaciones diplomaticas
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 20 de septiembre (ATCC) -- Se dio a la publicidad el dia 17 en Nueva York el comunicado conjunto sobre el establecimiento de las relaciones diplomaticas entre los gobiernos de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Emiratos Arabes Unidos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Segun el texto, partiendo del deseo mutuo de fomentar la comprension reciproca y fortalecer la amistad y cooperacion entre los pueblos de los dos paises y basandose en los principios y el objetivo de la carta de la ONU, en especial, en los derechos y tratados internacionales sobre el fomento de la paz y seguridad internacionales, la igualdad entre los Estados, la soberania nacional, la independencia, la integracion territorial, la no-intervencion en los asuntos internos de otros paises, los gobiernos de ambos paises acordaron establecer las relaciones diplomaticas a nivel de embajador a partir de la fecha en que firmaran el citado comunicado conjunto de acuerdo con los articulos de la Convencion de Viena del 18 de abril de 1961 sobre las relaciones diplomaticas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En representacion de los gobiernos de ambos paises, el documento fue rubricado por Pak Kil Yon, representante permanente y embajador extraordinario y plenipotenciario de la RPDC ante la ONU, y por su homologo del pais arabe, Ahmed Al-Jarman.

Cha Kum Chol emerge campeon mundial de levantamiento de pesas
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 20 de septiembre (ATCC) -- Cha Kum Chol conquisto la medalla de oro al levantar un total de 283 kg (128 kg en el arranque y 155 kg en el envion) en su division de 56 kg del Campeonato Mundial de Levantamiento de Pesas de 2007 (M), efectuado el dia 18. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El muchacho tambien se clasifico segundo en el arranque y el envion, respectivamente.

Rodong Sinmun aboga por la unidad pannacional
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 20 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El diario Rodong Sinmun publico en su edicion de este jueves un articulo individual subrayando que el logro de la unidad pannacional deviene la garantia decisiva de la reunificacion independiente y pacifica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La reunificacion de Corea no se propone a acabar con las contradicciones internas y las discrepancias entre los regimenes de ambas partes coreanas sino se orienta a reanudar la arteria nacional cortada por las fuerzas foraneas y lograr la conciliacion nacional, explica el articulista y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por tal razon, esa empresa tiene por su premisa mayor y contenido principal la unidad nacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Es una insoportable tragedia nacional el hecho de que la nacion coreana viene sufriendo durante mas de 60 anos las desgracias de la division en el Norte y en el Sur impuesta por las fuerzas foraneas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Lo fundamental de la reunificacion no reside en algun procedimiento o metodos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Si se logra la gran unidad pannacional basandose en la reconciliacion entre el Norte y el Sur y la union de voluntades de todos los coterraneos, se resolvera el problema fundamental de la reunificacion del pais. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por eso, este asunto resulta el motor principal y el factor determinante de esa causa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Cuando todos los coreanos se unan firmemente siendo fuerzas subjetivas de la reunificacion de la patria, esta causa se cumplira con exito. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La realidad de la actual epoca de reunificacion del 15 de junio, en que bajo la bandera del ideal de "Entre nosotros, los connacionales", la lucha por la reconciliacion y unidad nacionales se desarrolla en una etapa mas alta, corrobora el poderio y la vitalidad de la gran unidad pannacional como el motor de la causa de reunificacion independiente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esa cohesion puede ser lograda con exito si todos los compatriotas se fusionan compactamente bajo ese ideal, bandera de la unidad nacional, por encima de las diferencias de ideas y sistemas.
